ny, County Kilkenny, Ierland"},"en":{"–":"Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1418–Male":"1418–Deceased","Abt 1277":"about 1277","Abt 1314":"about 1314","Abt 1418":"about 1418","1418":"1418","Artane, County Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Ireland","Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland":"Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Holywood","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: of Norman origin, possibly a habitational name from Hollywood, Dublin.","Irish: adopted for Gaelic <b>Ó Cuileannáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cuileannán</i>’, a personal name apparently based on a diminutive of <i>cuileann</i> ‘holly tree’, and more commonly Anglicized as   Cullinan   or   Cullen  .","English: possibly a habitational name from any of various farms or hamlets in England called <i>Hollywood</i>, such as one in Sandon and Burston (Staffordshire), perhaps named with Middle English <i>holli</i> ‘holly’ + <i>wode</i> ‘wood’. However, the place is not on record before 1775, and all Hollywoods appear to be late."],"variants":[{"name":"Cullinan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Cormac.","Irish (Clare): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Cuileannáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cuileannán</i>’, from a diminutive of <i>Cuileann</i> (see   Cullen   2)."]}]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Roger Holywood was born as the son of JOHN (ROGER) (ROBERT) HOLYWOOD and MRS. JOHN (ROGER) (ROBERT) HOLYWOOD. He married HOLYWOOD about 1314, in Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1418–Male":"1418–Surnud","Abt 1277":"umbes 1277","Abt 1314":"umbes 1314","Abt 1418":"umbes 1418","1418":"1418","Artane, County Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Iirimaa","Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland":"Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1418–Male":"1418–Kuollut","Abt 1277":"noin 1277","Abt 1314":"noin 1314","Abt 1418":"noin 1418","1418":"1418","Artane, County Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Irlanti","Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland":"Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Irlanti"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1418–Male":"1418–Décédé","Abt 1277":"environ 1277","Abt 1314":"environ 1314","Abt 1418":"environ 1418","1418":"1418","Artane, County Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Irlande","Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland":"Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Irlande","lifeSummary":"Roger Holywood est né, fils de JOHN (ROGER) (ROBERT) HOLYWOOD et MRS. JOHN (ROGER) (ROBERT) HOLYWOOD. Il a épousé HOLYWOOD environ 1314, à Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Irlande. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1418–Male":"1418–Verstorben","Abt 1277":"um 1277","Abt 1314":"um 1314","Abt 1418":"um 1418","1418":"1418","Artane, County Dublin, Ireland":"Artane, County Dublin, Irland","Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Irelan